Kodō’s works were often attributed incorrectly to his contemporary, {{ill|Hiramatsu Baichi|ja|平松倍千|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hiramatsu Baichi|qq=}}, leading to centuries of confusion about his identity. This misattribution was only corrected in the mid-20th century when researchers such as Kanai Toranosuke identified Kodō as the true author of ''Nara Bōme Setsukai'' and other important historical texts.{{sfn|''Haikai Ima-miya-gusa Compiler''|p=389}}

