'''Kodō Murai''' (村井 古道, [[Tenna (Japan)|Tenna]] 1st year ([[1681]]) – [[Kan'en]] 2nd year [[October 14 (Lunisolar)|October 14]] ([[November 23]], [[1749]])) was a [[Edo period]] [[local historian]] of [[Nara]], a [[surgeon]], and a [[haiku poet]].

