== Biography ==

=== Early Life ===
Kodō Murai was born in [[Tenna (Japan)|Tenna]] 1st year (1681) in {{ill|Tōjōdo-chō|ja|東城戸町|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tōjōdo-chō|qq=}}, Nara. His father was Michihiro Murai, the author of ''{{ill|Nanto Meisho-shū|ja|南都名所集|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nanto Meisho-shū|qq=}}'' and also a haiku poet. Kodō later lived in {{ill|Nishijōdo-chō|ja|西城戸町|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nishijōdo-chō|qq=}} for much of his life.{{sfn|{{ill|Nanto Meisho-shū Compiler|ja|『俳諧今宮草』の編者無名園古道|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nanto Meisho-shū Compiler|qq=}}|p=401}} His real name was Katsukuro, and as a surgeon, he used the name Shōtetsu.{{sfn|''Haikai Ima-miya-gusa Compiler''|p=401}} Kodō’s most renowned pen name was "Mumeien Kodō," but he also used many other pseudonyms, including ''Dōsei,'' ''Suiko,'' ''Itsukawa Masuhito,'' ''Seifūken Murai Dōsei,'' and ''Sasagusa Sanjin Gengentoku Kodō.''{{sfn|''Haikai Ima-miya-gusa Compiler''|pp=399}}

